id: pm-kyd6
title: pm update --blocked-by does not create a pm deps graph edge
description: "Dogfood 2026-05-22 HIGH: pm update <id> --blocked-by pm-X stores blocked_by metadata but creates no edge in pm deps (edge_count:0). Agents that record blockers via the documented --blocked-by flag get an empty dependency graph and wrong what-is-blocking-me answers. Fix: have --blocked-by also create a blocks/blocked-by dependency edge (or unify the two concepts), so metadata and graph agree."
type: Issue
status: open
priority: 2
tags[0]:
created_at: "2026-05-22T15:44:30.773Z"
updated_at: "2026-05-23T03:48:21.098Z"
assignee: claude-code-agent
author: maintainer-agent
parent: pm-rnpb
comments[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-05-23T03:48:21.098Z",claude-code-agent,"FIXED (pm-uz25 step 1). Root cause: pm deps builds the graph only from the dependencies[] array, but update.ts --blocked-by wrote only the scalar blocked_by field (create.ts already added the edge; update.ts was asymmetric). Fix in src/cli/commands/update.ts: (1) new reconcileBlockedByDependency() helper; (2) resolve the --blocked-by target via locateItem before the synchronous mutate callback; (3) in the blocked_by mutate block, add a {kind:'blocked_by'} dependency edge when the target resolves, remove it on --unset blocked-by, and replace the stale edge on repoint. Verified by manual temp-dir smoke (edge_count 1->0) and 3 regression tests in update-command.spec.ts. update.ts is coverage-excluded so the 100% gate is unaffected."
body: ""
